verbose_text: The rationale behind choosing the latter ETS members was that ETS-1, the prototype of the ETS family, is overexpressed in latent as well as clinically manifest PCa, ETS-2 is also overexpressed in PCa, ETS-2 and ETS-1 play redundant roles, ETS-2 is associated with in vitro synthesized ETS-1, ETS-2 interacts with ERG in vivo demonstrated by the two-hybrid system and that ETV-4 is rearranged in PCa, similar to ERG.
